The author reflects on the Holocaust and expresses the need to remember and mourn the millions of Jews, as well as other groups, who were systematically killed during that time. They discuss the importance of passing on the lessons of the Holocaust to future generations and the responsibility to speak out against hate and antisemitism. The author also highlights the efforts of their administration to combat hate-fueled violence and support Holocaust survivors. They emphasize the need to defend foundational values such as freedom, equality, and dignity for all.